# LiteLLM code + documentation repos

When answering questions about LiteLLM behavior, configuration, or APIs:

1. Search **this repo** (`litellm/`, `tests/`, `ui/`, etc.) for implementation truth.
2. Also search the **`litellm-docs` workspace folder** (sibling clone or multi-root workspace) for user-facing documentation.
3. Do **not** add or edit documentation in this repo; doc changes belong in [BerriAI/litellm-docs](https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm-docs).
4. Published docs site: https://docs.litellm.ai

If only this repo is open and `litellm-docs` is not indexed, say so and use `@Docs` (https://docs.litellm.ai) or ask the user to open the multi-root workspace (`litellm-full.code-workspace`).
